Do you find yourself spending countless keystrokes searching StackOverflow for code help, creating a non-DRY search process that takes tons of time from your super productive day? Never fear, OverflowMe is here! 

Search StackOverflow right from your browser with this extension goodness. To use, simply type "so" (no quotes, of course) in your address bar, hit TAB, then enter your search terms. Hit the "enter" key and you're on your way! 

If you want to send praise or flame my super simple search extension, feel free to visit me at http://lynmuldrow.com to tell me all about it. This is also available as an open source thingy on my Github: https://github.com/lynmuldrow/OverflowMe

Enjoy!
